						<summary>

						<p>Second face of a pillar in the temple of Narēndrēśvarasvāmi.</p>						

						<p>DHĀTA.</p>						

						<p>This inscription can be assigned to 15th-16th centuries on the basis of paleography though it mentions the Cyclic year Dhāta, Māgha.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Refers to the consecration of Vīrēśvara by Jaluḍu Gaṁggiseṭṭi for the merit of his parents Linggisetti and Nāgammayamma.</p>						

						</summary>
